Supporting facts:
- Byte streams explicitly call `set_last_error(&err)` before returning drain errors; successful drains set `LAST_EXIT_CODE` to `0`.
- List stream drain errors are propagated with `?`; in tree eval, `eval_block` catches returned `Err` and calls `stack.set_last_error(err)`.
- In IR eval, caught errors routed to an error handler call `prepare_error_handler`, which both calls `ctx.stack.set_last_error(&error.item)` and stores `error.item.into_value(...)` in the error register.

