Minimal intended fix evidence: special-case `PipelineData::ByteStream` in `detect_columns`/`guess_width`; if it is an external child, use `stream.into_child()?.wait_with_output()?` and decode `stdout` without calling `check_ok`, so empty stdout from non-zero `grep` becomes empty input and yields `null`/empty behavior instead of `NonZeroExitCode`.

Relevant code evidence:

### `detect_columns.rs` imports

```rust
// crates/nu-command/src/strings/detect_columns.rs:1-4
use itertools::Itertools;
use nu_engine::command_prelude::*;
use nu_protocol::{Config, Range};
use std::{io::Cursor, iter::Peekable, str::CharIndices, sync::Arc};
```

### `DetectColumns::run` routes both normal and `--guess` paths through helpers that collect input

```rust
// crates/nu-command/src/strings/detect_columns.rs:103-127
fn run(
    &self,
    engine_state: &EngineState,
    stack: &mut Stack,
    call: &Call,
    input: PipelineData,
) -> Result<PipelineData, ShellError> {
    let num_rows_to_skip: Option<usize> = call.get_flag(engine_state, stack, "skip")?;
    let noheader = call.has_flag(engine_state, stack, "no-headers")?;
    let range: Option<Range> = call.get_flag(engine_state, stack, "combine-columns")?;
    let config = stack.get_config(engine_state);

    let args = Arguments {
        noheader,
        num_rows_to_skip,
        range,
        config,
    };

    if call.has_flag(engine_state, stack, "guess")? {
        guess_width(engine_state, call, input, args)
    } else {
        detect_columns(engine_state, call, input, args)
    }
}
```

### Current collection/output behavior in `guess_width`: uses `collect_string`; empty parsed result returns `nothing`

